  "text": "Apache Kafka broker-side SASL mechanism configuration validation occurs through a comprehensive chain of validations at startup. The process begins in KafkaConfig.scala (line 628-629) where sasl.mechanism.inter.broker.protocol is validated to be included in sasl.enabled.mechanisms. The key configuration constants are defined in BrokerSecurityConfigs.java (SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG, SASL_MECHANISM_INTER_BROKER_PROTOCOL_CONFIG). During SocketServer initialization, ChannelBuilders.serverChannelBuilder() creates the server channel builder which calls SaslChannelBuilder.configure() at lines 141-186. This method is critical and performs multiple validations: (1) it loads JAAS contexts for each enabled mechanism via JaasContext.loadServerContext() which validates presence of JAAS configuration entries (JaasContext.java lines 145-150) and ensures exactly one login module exists (lines 92-98); (2) it instantiates mechanism-specific callback handlers in createServerCallbackHandlers() (SaslChannelBuilder.java lines 317-336) which creates PlainServerCallbackHandler for PLAIN, ScramServerCallbackHandler for SCRAM mechanisms, and OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler for OAUTHBEARER; (3) it creates LoginManager instances for each mechanism via LoginManager.acquireLoginManager() (lines 170) which loads JAAS login contexts; (4) it configures each callback handler with mechanism parameters (line 151). For OAUTHBEARER specifically, OAuthBearerValidatorCallbackHandler.configure() (lines 106-114) delegates to getConfiguredInstance to instantiate the JwtValidator, and BrokerJwtValidator.configure() (lines 107-139) validates OAUTHBEARER-specific configuration like clock skew, audience, and issuer. For GSSAPI (lines 174-175), Kerberos-specific credentials are added from the subject. Finally, SaslServerAuthenticator constructor (lines 178-189) validates that sasl.enabled.mechanisms is non-empty and that callback handlers and subjects exist for each enabled mechanism. This multi-layered validation ensures broker startup fails fast if SASL mechanism configuration is incomplete or invalid."
